article.headline: North Texas 74, Western Kentucky 70
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis scored 16 points and hit the winning basket with 22 seconds left to help North Texas beat Western Kentucky 74-70 Saturday night. North Texas (16-7, 7-5) led by 12 points at halftime before Western Kentucky (17-8, 9-4) rallied. Davis' jumper from the right corner gave the Mean Green a 71-70 lead. Quincy Williams had 11 points and 12 rebounds, and Michael Sturns added 10 points for North Texas. Courtney Lee had 25 points and seven rebounds for Western Kentucky (17-8, 9-4). North Texas led 40-28 at halftime and held on despite hitting just 11-of-23 free throws in the second half. Tyrone Brazelton scored 12 points and Orlando Mendez-Valdez had 10 for the Hilltoppers.
